--- !u!114 &1215051094
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1215051069}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 533d3f483810c1146a52d21153bc055b, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  words: 'This is an example of the sequence interaction. notice how it is itself
    an interaction, but is calling several interactions in sequence. The interactor
    calls the sequence, and then the sequence calls the other interactions. for clarity,
    I tried to put the actions in order. It is a lot to look at. Another option would
    be to put each sequence in a child object, to help split up the busyness.


    I
    am not making a prefab of this because you would need to change out the specific
    Interactions, and the removed ones would still show as removed and take up space.

    Basically
    you can make it using any interactor (possibly not the basic one tho, since that
    takes all...) and then give it the sequence interactable, and then add the sequence.'
